ENTRY       EC 2.1.1.231                Enzyme
NAME        flavonoid 4'-O-methyltransferase;
            SOMT-2;
            4'-hydroxyisoflavone methyltransferase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Transferring one-carbon groups;
            Methyltransferases
SYSNAME     S-adenosyl-L-methionine:flavonoid 4'-O-methyltransferase
REACTION    S-adenosyl-L-methionine + a 4'-hydroxyflavanone = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + a 4'-methoxyflavanone [RN:R09792]
ALL_REAC    R09792
SUBSTRATE   S-adenosyl-L-methionine [CPD:C00019];
            4'-hydroxyflavanone [CPD:C19896]
PRODUCT     S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine [CPD:C00021];
            4'-methoxyflavanone [CPD:C19895]
COMMENT     The enzyme catalyses the 4'-methylation of naringenin. In vitro it catalyses the 4'-methylation of apigenin, quercetin, daidzein and genistein.
HISTORY     EC 2.1.1.231 created 2011
REFERENCE   1  [PMID:15961179]
  AUTHORS   Kim DH, Kim BG, Lee Y, Ryu JY, Lim Y, Hur HG, Ahn JH
  TITLE     Regiospecific methylation of naringenin to ponciretin by soybean O-methyltransferase expressed in Escherichia coli.
  JOURNAL   J. Biotechnol. 119 (2005) 155-62.
  ORGANISM  Glycine max
